> We're not too proud nor too grown up to admit that this recipe may have been inspired by a certain canine cartoon. Unfortunately Lady and the Tramp didn't provide recipe details so instead we took our inspiration from Tuscany to create a rustic, hearty dish that can be whipped up in no time at all.

== Meatball Mixture ==

First soak your @dried porcini mushrooms{1} in hot (not boiling) water. Break up the
@Carr's crackers{2} and soak them in half a cup of @milk{1/2%cup} if you have it (or
some water if not).

Dice up the @garlic clove{1}(diced finely) and @echalion shallot{1}(diced finely) and
tear up the @basil{1/2}(torn into leaves). The porcini mushrooms should soften up after
about ~{5%minutes}. Drain them, squeeze all the water out with your hand and then dice
them finely. Squeeze out the crackers too.

Mix the @minced beef{250%g}, half the garlic, @dried oregano{1}, and 3/4 of the
@Pecorino cheese{1.5}(grated, save some for the garnish).

Next add the crackers, porcini mushrooms, @salt{1/4%tsp} and a good pinch of
@black pepper{pinch}. Work the mixture with your hands for a few ~{minutes}.

== Tomato Sauce ==

Put a #non-stick pan{} on medium-low heat and add @olive oil{2%tsp}. Gently fry the
shallot and remaining garlic for ~{5%minutes} before adding in the
@chopped tomatoes{1}, a pinch of salt, pepper and @?sugar{pinch} (if you have it).
Bubble away until the sauce has gone nice and thick.

== Meatballs ==

Roll the meat into compact balls just slightly smaller than a golf ball. Finally, roll
them in the @couscous{1.5}(rolled in).

> See our Fresh Tip below to use couscous for a great, crunchy finish.

== Spaghetti and Frying ==

Bring a #pot{} of water to the boil, add in your @wheat spaghetti{220} with
@salt{1/2%tsp}. Cook for around ~{10%minutes} until 'al dente' (i.e. there is just a
hint of firmness left in the middle).

Heat @olive oil{1%tbsp} on medium-high heat and brown off your meatballs. Cook on all
sides for around ~{6%minutes} in total at which point they should be cooked through.

> Turn your meatballs gently so as not to break them.

== Serving ==

Once your meatballs are cooked stir the basil into your tomato sauce then pour this
over the meatballs. Drain your pasta and divide it into bowls before topping with your
meatballs, sauce and a sprinkle of pecorino.